This is the adapter that bridges the Rust CLI to Claude via the Anthropic Messages API — a thin, model-specific transport that executes the summarizer prompt against a chosen model and returns the completion verbatim.

It reads `{"system", "user", "model"}` from stdin (the system prompt, runner-assembled dynamic data, and model name chosen by the CLI's `--model` flag), calls the Messages API once with prompt caching enabled on the system block, and writes the completion to stdout; all exit codes and errors go to stderr. No prompt assembly happens here — it honors the decoupling rule in `prompts/README.md` and adds zero instructions of its own.

The system prompt is sent as a cached ephemeral block because the summarizer reuses one identical prompt across every leaf/rollup call in a task, making caching a material cost/latency win. Reasoning is locked down (thinking disabled, `output_config` effort "low") since summarization is a short, strict task — except haiku models, which reject the `effort` param outright (HTTP 400), so they get neither.

Reads API key from `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (required), base URL from `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` (default: `https://api.anthropic.com`), max tokens from `CTX_AGENT_MAX_TOKENS` (default: 2048), and temperature is fixed at 0 (not exposed as a knob — stable output for strict format). `extract_text()` concatenates all text content blocks from the response and dies if the result is empty; `call_api()` handles HTTP errors with the full response body on stderr for debugging.